frameDefinitions: An Event takes place at a Place and Time.
A Process comes to an end.
A Process is finished and can no longer proceed.
An Agent changes a Part of a complex entity with regard to some Feature in order to achieve some Imposed_purpose affected by the Feature.
An Entity is declared to exist, generally irrespective of its position or even the possibility of its position being specified.

The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
frameExamples: Big earthquakes only <t>happen</t> along plate boundaries. INI
I need to <t>adjust</t> the thermostat to around 80 degrees when she visits.
Finally, Poland ceased to <t>exist</t> as a state for hundreds of years.
